</form><html xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:math="java.lang.Math" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:xs="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions" xmlns:xdt="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-datatypes" xmlns:caml="http://lc.ca.gov/legalservices/schemas/caml.1#" xmlns:xhtml="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><head><title>SCR153:v99#DOCUMENT</title><meta name="dc:identifier" content="SCR153"/><meta name="dc:title" content="SCR &#xA;              153-&#xA;                INTRODUCED&#xA;              "/><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=utf-8"/></head><body><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Start</h2></span><div id="bill_all" align="justify"><div id="about"><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td align="center"/></tr></tbody></table></div><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><font size="3" style="FONT-FAMILY: MinionPC, Arial Unicode MS">
                    CALIFORNIA LEGISLATURE—
                    2025–2026 REGULAR SESSION</font></div><br clear="all"/><span id="bill_house_num"><div style="float: left; width:50%; font-weight: bold; "><span style="text-transform: uppercase; text-align:left;width:50%;"><b>
                Senate Concurrent Resolution
              </b></span></div><div style="float:right; width:50%; text-align:right;"><span style="text-transform: uppercase;"><b>No. 153</b></span></div></span><hr/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><table style="border-collapse: collapse" cellSpacing="0" align="center" role="presentation"><tbody><tr><td id="bill_authors" align="center"><span style="font-weight:bold;">Introduced by Senator Grove<br/>(Coauthors: Senators Choi, Ochoa Bogh, and Seyarto)<br/></span></td></tr><tr><td id="bill_intro_date" align="center" class="textcenter"><br/>April 06, 2026</td></tr></tbody></table></div><hr/><br clear="all"/><div id="title"><span style="font-weight:normal;font-size:0.9em;"> Relative to National Day of Prayer. </span></div><br clear="all"/><br clear="all"/><div align="center"><h2>LEGISLATIVE COUNSEL'S DIGEST</h2></div><br/><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0"><span id="subject">SCR 153, as introduced, Grove.
                          National Day of Prayer.</span></div><div><span id="digesttext"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">This measure would recognize May 7, 2026, as the National Day of Prayer.</div></span></div><span class="hidden"><h2>Digest Key</h2></span><span id="fiscalcommittee">
      Fiscal Committee:
      <span style=" text-transform: lowercase">NO</span>  </span></div><hr/><span class="hidden"><h2>Bill Text</h2></span><span class="Resolution" title="source: /caml:MeasureDoc/caml:Resolution&#xA;    "><span class="Whereas" id="id_54B216DD-7520-400E-B814-F89C1059505C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The National Day of Prayer is observed each year on the first Thursday of May as a time when Americans are invited to come together in prayer and seek God’s guidance for our communities, our state, and our nation; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_FC4B2DD4-508D-4478-B14E-9912C26413B2"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, From the founding of the United States, national leaders have acknowledged the importance of prayer and have called upon the country to turn to God during moments of challenge and uncertainty; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_5343C20B-7B45-4AEB-A1CF-EF8576D8309B"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, Faith has been a defining influence throughout American history, shaping the values, perseverance, and unity of the American people; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_1E238701-12F5-432E-BD94-3866E940AC76"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The United States has consistently affirmed that prayer is a source of strength in both public and private life, reminding the nation that reliance on God has guided Americans through times of trial and triumph; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_D56077EC-EED8-475E-A2AE-F7E7E757F394"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, California’s diverse faith communities continue to strengthen neighborhoods by supporting families, caring for the vulnerable, and fostering a spirit of service and hope; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_889FD884-6155-489C-B96B-CD291B1D88CA"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, The National Day of Prayer encourages individuals and communities to set aside time to seek God’s direction for the future of our state and nation and to pray for the well-being of those who serve in positions of leadership and public trust; and</div></span><span class="Whereas" id="id_E3873578-782D-43B4-BDB4-00FFB10BE975"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">WHEREAS, This day provides all Californians with an opportunity to recognize the nation’s enduring ties to faith and to ask for God’s protection, wisdom, and peace; now, therefore, be it</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_49B13AF4-CE3A-412E-85E1-4CF52C0D8285"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved by the Senate of the State of California, the Assembly thereof concurring, That the Legislature hereby recognizes May 7, 2026, as the National Day of Prayer; and be it further</div></span><span class="Resolved" id="id_F2E178E5-0232-4F13-B976-88C63FB21D8C"><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">Resolved, That the Secretary of the Senate transmit copies of this resolution to the author for appropriate distribution.</div></span></span></div></body></html>
